<br>
The point was mainly that the case is not some outrageous verdict - it's a very reasonable one.<br>
<br>
People too easily get caught up in what they THINK the burns were - the kind you would expect from hot coffee. They don't see the issue was the EXCESSIVE burns, because the coffee was negligently kept 20 degrees hotter than competitors and 50 degrees hotter than home makers.<br>
<br>
In a trial you have to by the evidence you have there; the evidence reported was that 185 degree coffee causes burns in 2 to 7 seconds, while home made coffee takes 60 seconds to cause the burns.<br>
<br>
Picture the damage you expect to have from spilling coffee on yourself - and now, picture pieces of your flesh hanging loose, in your groin and thighs, with skin grafts and months of painful recovery, and ask if you don't see the difference.<br>
<br>
